      </structure>
    </statement>
    <statement id="582.txt-9">
      <text>Phyllaries 4–7, erect in fruit, lanceolate in flower, becoming ovate-lanceolate in fruit, midveins and sometimes secondary veins becoming prominent in fruit, curving inward at bases to form keels, apices acute .</text>
      <structure id="o12074" name="phyllary">
